# Deny-list, not an allow-list: the `runtime` stage builds the framework wheel from
# the `angee/` + `addons/` source roots, so they (and the manifests) must stay in the
# build context. Drop only VCS, virtualenvs, generated/state, caches, node_modules,
# the JS workspace, and the example project — none are copied by any stage, and
# hatch-angee already excludes web/node_modules from the wheel itself.
.git
.venv
.angee
**/node_modules
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/runtime
.mypy_cache
.pytest_cache
.ruff_cache
packages
examples
.work
docs/screenshots
test-results
playwright-report
.playwright-mcp
dist
build
*.egg-info
